Former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela has finally admitted that she is responsible for R470 000 due for the repairs of her state BMW that was crashed by her son. Madonsela also admitted that her refusal to pay back the money displayed poor judgement and low moral standard.Last week thousands took to social media and expressed anger at Madonsela for refusing to pay for the demages.&#8220;Those of us who believe in a better world must be the first to do what we believe is right&#8230;.,&#8221; said Madonsela in a letter. comments